decl: example : s ∩ t ∪ s ∩ u ⊆ s ∩ (t ∪ u)
og_raw:
example : s ∩ t ∪ s ∩ u ⊆ s ∩ (t ∪ u)  := by
  rintro x (⟨xs, xt⟩ | ⟨xs, xu⟩)
  · use xs; left; exact xt
  . use xs; right; exact xu
new_raw:

  rintro x (⟨xs, xt⟩ | ⟨xs, xu⟩)
  · use xs; left; exact xt
  . use xs; right; exact xu

decl: example : s \ (t ∪ u) ⊆ (s \ t) \ u
og_raw:
example : s \ (t ∪ u) ⊆ (s \ t) \ u  := by
  rintro x ⟨xs, xntu⟩
  constructor
  use xs
  · intro xt
    exact xntu (Or.inl xt)
  intro xu
  apply xntu (Or.inr xu)
new_raw:
example : s \ (t ∪ u) ⊆ (s \ t) \ u    := by
  rintro x ⟨xs, xntu⟩
  have x_not_in_t : x ∉ t := by
    intro xt
    exact xntu (Or.inl xt)
  have x_not_in_u : x ∉ u := by
    intro xu
    exact xntu (Or.inr xu)
  have x_in_s_diff_t : x ∈ s \ t := ⟨xs, x_not_in_t⟩
  constructor
  . exact x_in_s_diff_t
  . exact x_not_in_u

decl: example : { n | Nat.Prime n } ∩ { n | n > 2 } ⊆ { n | ¬Even n }
og_raw:
example : { n | Nat.Prime n } ∩ { n | n > 2 } ⊆ { n | ¬Even n }  := by
  intro n
  simp
  intro nprime
  rcases Nat.Prime.eq_two_or_odd nprime with h | h
  · rw [h]
    intro
    linarith
  rw [Nat.even_iff, h]
  norm_num
new_raw:
example : { n | Nat.Prime n } ∩ { n | n > 2 } ⊆ { n | ¬Even n }    := by
  intro n
  simp
  intro nprime
  have h_cases : n = 2 ∨ n % 2 = 1 := Nat.Prime.eq_two_or_odd nprime
  have case_2_lt_2 : ¬(2 < 2) := by linarith
  rcases h_cases with h | h
  · rw [h]
    intro h_lt
    contradiction
  · rw [Nat.even_iff, h]
    norm_num

decl: example (h₀ : ∀ x ∈ t, ¬Even x) (h₁ : ∀ x ∈ t, Prime x) : ∀ x ∈ s, ¬Even x ∧ Prime x
og_raw:
example (h₀ : ∀ x ∈ t, ¬Even x) (h₁ : ∀ x ∈ t, Prime x) : ∀ x ∈ s, ¬Even x ∧ Prime x  := by
  intro x xs
  constructor
  · apply h₀ x (ssubt xs)
  apply h₁ x (ssubt xs)
new_raw:
example (h₀ : ∀ x ∈ t, ¬Even x) (h₁ : ∀ x ∈ t, Prime x) : ∀ x ∈ s, ¬Even x ∧ Prime x   := by
  intro x xs
  have x_in_t := ssubt xs
  have not_even_x := h₀ x x_in_t
  have prime_x := h₁ x x_in_t
  constructor
  exact not_even_x
  exact prime_x

new_raw:
example (h : ∃ x ∈ s, ¬Even x ∧ Prime x) : ∃ x ∈ t, Prime x  := by

og_raw:
example : (s ∪ ⋂ i, A i) = ⋂ i, A i ∪ s  := by
  ext x
  simp only [mem_union, mem_iInter]

  · rintro (xs | xI)
    · intro i
      right
      exact xs
    intro i
    left

  · left
    exact xs
  right
  intro i
  cases h i
  · assumption
  contradiction

decl: example : (⋃ p ∈ primes, { x | x ≤ p }) = univ
og_raw:
example : (⋃ p ∈ primes, { x | x ≤ p }) = univ  := by
  apply eq_univ_of_forall
  intro x
  simp
  rcases Nat.exists_infinite_primes x with ⟨p, pge, primep⟩
  use p, primep
new_raw:
example : (⋃ p ∈ primes, { x | x ≤ p }) = univ   := by
  apply eq_univ_of_forall
  intro x
  simp
  have prime_ge_x : ∃ p, p ≥ x ∧ Nat.Prime p := Nat.exists_infinite_primes x
  rcases prime_ge_x with ⟨p, pge, primep⟩
  use p
  exact ⟨primep, pge⟩

decl: theorem sb_right_inv {x : α} (hx : x ∉ sbSet f g) : g (invFun g x) = x
og_raw:
theorem sb_right_inv {x : α} (hx : x ∉ sbSet f g) : g (invFun g x) = x  := by
  have : x ∈ g '' univ := by
    contrapose! hx
    rw [sbSet, mem_iUnion]
    use 0
    rw [sbAux, mem_diff]
    exact ⟨mem_univ _, hx⟩
  have : ∃ y, g y = x := by
    simp at this
    assumption
  exact invFun_eq this
new_raw:
theorem sb_right_inv {x : α} (hx : x ∉ sbSet f g) : g (invFun g x) = x  := by
  have : x ∈ g '' univ := by
    contrapose! hx
    rw [sbSet, mem_iUnion]
    use 0
    rw [sbAux, mem_diff]
    exact ⟨mem_univ _, hx⟩
  have : ∃ y, g y = x := by
    simp at this
    assumption
  exact invFun_eq this

decl: theorem sb_injective (hf : Injective f) : Injective (sbFun f g)
og_raw:
theorem sb_injective (hf : Injective f) : Injective (sbFun f g)  := by
  set A := sbSet f g with A_def
  set h := sbFun f g with h_def
  intro x₁ x₂
  intro (hxeq : h x₁ = h x₂)
  show x₁ = x₂
  simp only [h_def, sbFun, ← A_def] at hxeq
  by_cases xA : x₁ ∈ A ∨ x₂ ∈ A
  · wlog x₁A : x₁ ∈ A generalizing x₁ x₂ hxeq xA
    · symm
      apply this hxeq.symm xA.symm (xA.resolve_left x₁A)
    have x₂A : x₂ ∈ A := by
      apply _root_.not_imp_self.mp
      intro (x₂nA : x₂ ∉ A)
      rw [if_pos x₁A, if_neg x₂nA] at hxeq
      rw [A_def, sbSet, mem_iUnion] at x₁A
      have x₂eq : x₂ = g (f x₁) := by
        rw [hxeq, sb_right_inv f g x₂nA]
      rcases x₁A with ⟨n, hn⟩
      rw [A_def, sbSet, mem_iUnion]
      use n + 1
      simp [sbAux]
      exact ⟨x₁, hn, x₂eq.symm⟩
    rw [if_pos x₁A, if_pos x₂A] at hxeq
    exact hf hxeq
  push_neg  at xA
  rw [if_neg xA.1, if_neg xA.2] at hxeq
  rw [← sb_right_inv f g xA.1, hxeq, sb_right_inv f g xA.2]
new_raw:
theorem sb_injective (hf : Injective f) : Injective (sbFun f g)  := by
  set A := sbSet f g with A_def
  set h := sbFun f g with h_def
  intro x₁ x₂
  intro (hxeq : h x₁ = h x₂)
  show x₁ = x₂
  simp only [h_def, sbFun, ← A_def] at hxeq
  by_cases xA : x₁ ∈ A ∨ x₂ ∈ A
  · wlog x₁A : x₁ ∈ A generalizing x₁ x₂ hxeq xA
    · symm
      apply this hxeq.symm xA.symm (xA.resolve_left x₁A)
    have x₂A : x₂ ∈ A := by
      apply _root_.not_imp_self.mp
      intro (x₂nA : x₂ ∉ A)
      rw [if_pos x₁A, if_neg x₂nA] at hxeq
      rw [A_def, sbSet, mem_iUnion] at x₁A
      have x₂eq : x₂ = g (f x₁) := by
        rw [hxeq, sb_right_inv f g x₂nA]
      rcases x₁A with ⟨n, hn⟩
      rw [A_def, sbSet, mem_iUnion]
      use n + 1
      simp [sbAux]
      exact ⟨x₁, hn, x₂eq.symm⟩
    rw [if_pos x₁A, if_pos x₂A] at hxeq
    exact hf hxeq
  push_neg  at xA
  rw [if_neg xA.1, if_neg xA.2] at hxeq
  rw [← sb_right_inv f g xA.1, hxeq, sb_right_inv f g xA.2]

decl: theorem sb_surjective (hg : Injective g) : Surjective (sbFun f g)
og_raw:
theorem sb_surjective (hg : Injective g) : Surjective (sbFun f g)  := by
  set A := sbSet f g with A_def
  set h := sbFun f g with h_def
  intro y
  by_cases gyA : g y ∈ A
  · rw [A_def, sbSet, mem_iUnion] at gyA
    rcases gyA with ⟨n, hn⟩
    rcases n with _ | n
    · simp [sbAux] at hn
    simp [sbAux] at hn
    rcases hn with ⟨x, xmem, hx⟩
    use x
    have : x ∈ A := by
      rw [A_def, sbSet, mem_iUnion]
      exact ⟨n, xmem⟩
    simp only [h_def, sbFun, if_pos this]
    exact hg hx
  use g y
  simp only [h_def, sbFun, if_neg gyA]
  apply leftInverse_invFun hg
new_raw:
theorem sb_surjective (hg : Injective g) : Surjective (sbFun f g)  := by
  set A := sbSet f g with A_def
  set h := sbFun f g with h_def
  intro y
  by_cases gyA : g y ∈ A
  · rw [A_def, sbSet, mem_iUnion] at gyA
    rcases gyA with ⟨n, hn⟩
    rcases n with _ | n
    · simp [sbAux] at hn
    simp [sbAux] at hn
    rcases hn with ⟨x, xmem, hx⟩
    use x
    have : x ∈ A := by
      rw [A_def, sbSet, mem_iUnion]
      exact ⟨n, xmem⟩
    simp only [h_def, sbFun, if_pos this]
    exact hg hx
  use g y
  simp only [h_def, sbFun, if_neg gyA]
  apply leftInverse_invFun hg

decl: example : f '' s ⊆ v ↔ s ⊆ f ⁻¹' v
og_raw:
example : f '' s ⊆ v ↔ s ⊆ f ⁻¹' v  := by
  constructor
  · intro h x xs
    have : f x ∈ f '' s := mem_image_of_mem _ xs
    exact h this
  intro h y ymem
  rcases ymem with ⟨x, xs, fxeq⟩
  rw [← fxeq]
  apply h xs
new_raw:
example : f '' s ⊆ v ↔ s ⊆ f ⁻¹' v   := by
  constructor
  · intro h x xs
    have fx_mem_image := mem_image_of_mem f xs
    exact h fx_mem_image
  · intro h y ymem
    rcases ymem with ⟨x, xs, fxeq⟩
    have fx_in_v := h xs
    rw [← fxeq]
    exact fx_in_v

decl: example (h : Injective f) : f ⁻¹' (f '' s) ⊆ s
og_raw:
example (h : Injective f) : f ⁻¹' (f '' s) ⊆ s  := by
  rintro x ⟨y, ys, fxeq⟩
  rw [← h fxeq]
  exact ys
new_raw:
example (h : Injective f) : f ⁻¹' (f '' s) ⊆ s     := by
  rintro x ⟨y, ys, fxeq⟩
  have h_eq : f y = f x := fxeq
  have h_inj : Injective f := h
  have h_inv : y = x := h_inj h_eq
  have h_y_in_s : y ∈ s := ys
  have subst_eq : x = y := h_inv.symm
  rw [subst_eq]
  exact h_y_in_s

decl: example : f '' (f ⁻¹' u) ⊆ u
og_raw:
example : f '' (f ⁻¹' u) ⊆ u  := by
  rintro y ⟨x, xmem, rfl⟩
  exact xmem
new_raw:
example : f '' (f ⁻¹' u) ⊆ u   := by
  rintro y ⟨x, hx_mem, rfl⟩
  have h_fx_in_u : f x ∈ u := hx_mem
  exact h_fx_in_u

decl: example (h : Surjective f) : u ⊆ f '' (f ⁻¹' u)
og_raw:
example (h : Surjective f) : u ⊆ f '' (f ⁻¹' u)  := by
  intro y yu
  rcases h y with ⟨x, fxeq⟩
  use x
  constructor
  · show f x ∈ u
    rw [fxeq]
    exact yu
  exact fxeq
new_raw:
example (h : Surjective f) : u ⊆ f '' (f ⁻¹' u)   := by
  intro y yu
  have h_surj : ∃ x, f x = y := h y
  rcases h_surj with ⟨x, fxeq⟩
  have fx_in_u : f x ∈ u := by rw [fxeq]; exact yu
  use x
  constructor
  show x ∈ f ⁻¹' u
  exact fx_in_u
  exact fxeq

decl: example (h : s ⊆ t) : f '' s ⊆ f '' t
og_raw:
example (h : s ⊆ t) : f '' s ⊆ f '' t  := by
  rintro y ⟨x, xs, fxeq⟩
  use x, h xs
new_raw:
example (h : s ⊆ t) : f '' s ⊆ f '' t    := by
  rintro y ⟨x, xs, fxeq⟩
  have xt : x ∈ t := h xs
  have y_in_t : y ∈ f '' t := ⟨x, xt, fxeq⟩
  exact y_in_t

decl: example (h : u ⊆ v) : f ⁻¹' u ⊆ f ⁻¹' v
og_raw:
example (h : u ⊆ v) : f ⁻¹' u ⊆ f ⁻¹' v  := by
  intro x; apply h
new_raw:
example (h : u ⊆ v) : f ⁻¹' u ⊆ f ⁻¹' v    := by
  intro x
  have fx_in_u : f x ∈ u ↔ x ∈ f ⁻¹' u := by
    simp
  have fx_in_v : f x ∈ v ↔ x ∈ f ⁻¹' v := by
    simp
  have implication : (f x ∈ u → f x ∈ v) ↔ (x ∈ f ⁻¹' u → x ∈ f ⁻¹' v) := by
    rw [fx_in_u, fx_in_v]
  apply implication.mpr
  intro fxu
  apply h
  exact fxu

decl: example : f ⁻¹' (u ∪ v) = f ⁻¹' u ∪ f ⁻¹' v
og_raw:
example : f ⁻¹' (u ∪ v) = f ⁻¹' u ∪ f ⁻¹' v  := by
  ext x; rfl
new_raw:
example : f ⁻¹' (u ∪ v) = f ⁻¹' u ∪ f ⁻¹' v     := by
  ext x
  have h1 : x ∈ f ⁻¹' (u ∪ v) ↔ f x ∈ u ∪ v := Iff.rfl
  have h2 : f x ∈ u ∪ v ↔ (f x ∈ u ∨ f x ∈ v) := Iff.rfl
  have h3 : x ∈ f ⁻¹' u ∪ f ⁻¹' v ↔ (x ∈ f ⁻¹' u ∨ x ∈ f ⁻¹' v) := Iff.rfl
  have h4 : x ∈ f ⁻¹' u ↔ f x ∈ u := Iff.rfl
  have h5 : x ∈ f ⁻¹' v ↔ f x ∈ v := Iff.rfl
  have h6 : f x ∈ u ∨ f x ∈ v ↔ x ∈ f ⁻¹' u ∨ x ∈ f ⁻¹' v := by rw [h4, h5]
  have h7 : x ∈ f ⁻¹' (u ∪ v) ↔ (f x ∈ u ∨ f x ∈ v) := by rw [h1, h2]
  have h8 : x ∈ f ⁻¹' u ∪ f ⁻¹' v ↔ (x ∈ f ⁻¹' u ∨ x ∈ f ⁻¹' v) := h3
  rw [h1, h2, h3, h6]

decl: example : f '' (s ∩ t) ⊆ f '' s ∩ f '' t
og_raw:
example : f '' (s ∩ t) ⊆ f '' s ∩ f '' t  := by

  . use x, xs
  . use x, xt
new_raw:
example : f '' (s ∩ t) ⊆ f '' s ∩ f '' t   := by
  rintro y ⟨x, ⟨xs, xt⟩, rfl⟩
  have h1 : f x ∈ f '' s := ⟨x, xs, rfl⟩
  have h2 : f x ∈ f '' t := ⟨x, xt, rfl⟩
  exact ⟨h1, h2⟩

  use x₁
  constructor
  . use x₁s

    exact x₂t

example (h : Injective f) : f '' s ∩ f '' t ⊆ f '' (s ∩ t)  := by
  rintro y ⟨⟨x₁, x₁s, rfl⟩, ⟨x₂, x₂t, fx₂eq⟩⟩

decl: example : f '' s \ f '' t ⊆ f '' (s \ t)
og_raw:
example : f '' s \ f '' t ⊆ f '' (s \ t)  := by
  rintro y ⟨⟨x₁, x₁s, rfl⟩, h⟩
  use x₁
  constructor
  . constructor
    . exact x₁s
    . intro h'
      apply h
      use x₁, h'
  . rfl
new_raw:
example : f '' s \ f '' t ⊆ f '' (s \ t)   := by
  rintro y ⟨⟨x₁, x₁s, rfl⟩, h⟩
  have hx₁s : x₁ ∈ s := x₁s
  have hnotin : f x₁ ∉ f '' t := h
  have hx₁notin_t : x₁ ∉ t := by
    intro h'
    apply hnotin
    use x₁, h'
  use x₁
  constructor
  exact ⟨hx₁s, hx₁notin_t⟩
  rfl

example : f '' (s ∩ f ⁻¹' u) ⊆ f '' s ∩ u   := by

  have hx_in_s : x ∈ s := xs
  have hx_in_preimage_u : x ∈ f ⁻¹' u := fxu
  have hy_in_image_s : f x ∈ f '' s := ⟨x, hx_in_s, rfl⟩
  have hy_in_u : f x ∈ u := hx_in_preimage_u
  exact ⟨hy_in_image_s, hy_in_u⟩

decl: example : (f ⁻¹' ⋃ i, B i) = ⋃ i, f ⁻¹' B i
og_raw:
example : (f ⁻¹' ⋃ i, B i) = ⋃ i, f ⁻¹' B i  := by
  ext x
  simp
new_raw:
example : (f ⁻¹' ⋃ i, B i) = ⋃ i, f ⁻¹' B i   := by
  ext x
  have h1 : x ∈ f ⁻¹' ⋃ i, B i ↔ f x ∈ ⋃ i, B i := by simp
  have h2 : (f x ∈ ⋃ i, B i) ↔ (∃ i, f x ∈ B i) := by simp
  have h3 : x ∈ ⋃ i, f ⁻¹' B i ↔ (∃ i, x ∈ f ⁻¹' B i) := by simp
  have h4 : (∃ i, x ∈ f ⁻¹' B i) ↔ (∃ i, f x ∈ B i) := by simp
  rw [h1, h2, h3, h4]

decl: example : (f ⁻¹' ⋂ i, B i) = ⋂ i, f ⁻¹' B i

decl: example : InjOn sqrt { x | x ≥ 0 }
og_raw:
example : InjOn sqrt { x | x ≥ 0 }  := by
  intro x xnonneg y ynonneg
  intro e
  calc
    x = sqrt x ^ 2 := by rw [sq_sqrt xnonneg]
    _ = sqrt y ^ 2 := by rw [e]
    _ = y := by rw [sq_sqrt ynonneg]
new_raw:
example : InjOn sqrt { x | x ≥ 0 }    := by
  intro x xnonneg y ynonneg
  intro e
  have hx_eq : x = sqrt x ^ 2 := by rw [sq_sqrt xnonneg]
  have hy_eq : y = sqrt y ^ 2 := by rw [sq_sqrt ynonneg]
  have sqrt_eq : sqrt x = sqrt y := by exact e
  have heq : sqrt x ^ 2 = sqrt y ^ 2 := by rw [sqrt_eq]
  rw [hx_eq, hy_eq, heq]

decl: example : InjOn (fun x ↦ x ^ 2) { x : ℝ | x ≥ 0 }
og_raw:
example : InjOn (fun x ↦ x ^ 2) { x : ℝ | x ≥ 0 }  := by
  intro x xnonneg y ynonneg
  intro e
  dsimp at *
  calc
    x = sqrt (x ^ 2) := by rw [sqrt_sq xnonneg]
    _ = sqrt (y ^ 2) := by rw [e]
    _ = y := by rw [sqrt_sq ynonneg]
new_raw:
example : InjOn (fun x ↦ x ^ 2) { x : ℝ | x ≥ 0 }    := by
  intro x xnonneg y ynonneg
  intro e
  dsimp at *
  have h1 : x = sqrt (x ^ 2) := by rw [sqrt_sq xnonneg]
  have h2 : sqrt (x ^ 2) = sqrt (y ^ 2) := by rw [e]
  have h3 : sqrt (y ^ 2) = y := by rw [sqrt_sq ynonneg]
  have h4 : x = sqrt (y ^ 2) := by rw [h1, h2]
  calc
    x = sqrt (x ^ 2) := h1
    _ = sqrt (y ^ 2) := h2
    _ = y := h3

decl: example : sqrt '' { x | x ≥ 0 } = { y | y ≥ 0 }
og_raw:
example : sqrt '' { x | x ≥ 0 } = { y | y ≥ 0 }  := by
  ext y; constructor
  · rintro ⟨x, ⟨xnonneg, rfl⟩⟩
    apply sqrt_nonneg
  intro ynonneg
  use y ^ 2
  dsimp at *
  constructor
  apply pow_nonneg ynonneg
  apply sqrt_sq
  assumption
new_raw:
example : sqrt '' { x | x ≥ 0 } = { y | y ≥ 0 }   := by
  ext y; constructor
  · rintro ⟨x, xnonneg, rfl⟩
    have : x ≥ 0 := xnonneg
    exact sqrt_nonneg x
  · intro ynonneg
    have hy_nonneg : y ≥ 0 := ynonneg
    have hsq_nonneg : y ^ 2 ≥ 0 := pow_nonneg hy_nonneg 2
    use y ^ 2
    have hsq_sqrt : sqrt (y ^ 2) = y := sqrt_sq hy_nonneg
    exact ⟨hsq_nonneg, hsq_sqrt⟩

decl: example : (range fun x ↦ x ^ 2) = { y : ℝ | y ≥ 0 }
og_raw:
example : (range fun x ↦ x ^ 2) = { y : ℝ | y ≥ 0 }  := by
  ext y
  constructor
  · rintro ⟨x, rfl⟩
    dsimp at *
    apply pow_two_nonneg
  intro ynonneg
  use sqrt y
  exact sq_sqrt ynonneg
new_raw:
example : (range fun x ↦ x ^ 2) = { y : ℝ | y ≥ 0 }   := by
  ext y
  constructor
  · rintro ⟨x, rfl⟩
    have h_nonneg : ∀ x : ℝ, 0 ≤ x ^ 2 := by intro x; apply pow_two_nonneg
    dsimp at *
    exact h_nonneg x
  intro ynonneg
  have h_sqrt : ∀ y : ℝ, 0 ≤ y → (sqrt y) ^ 2 = y := by intro y h; exact sq_sqrt h
  use sqrt y
  exact h_sqrt y ynonneg

decl: theorem inverse_spec {f : α → β} (y : β) (h : ∃ x, f x = y) : f (inverse f y) = y
og_raw:
theorem inverse_spec {f : α → β} (y : β) (h : ∃ x, f x = y) : f (inverse f y) = y  := by
  rw [inverse, dif_pos h]
  exact Classical.choose_spec h
new_raw:
theorem inverse_spec {f : α → β} (y : β) (h : ∃ x, f x = y) : f (inverse f y) = y   := by
  rw [inverse, dif_pos h]
  have : f (Classical.choose h) = y := Classical.choose_spec h
  exact this

decl: example : Injective f ↔ LeftInverse (inverse f) f
og_raw:
example : Injective f ↔ LeftInverse (inverse f) f  := by
  constructor
  · intro h y
    apply h
    apply inverse_spec
    use y
  intro h x1 x2 e
  rw [← h x1, ← h x2, e]
new_raw:
example : Injective f ↔ LeftInverse (inverse f) f   := by
  constructor
  · intro h
    have h_spec : ∀ x, f (inverse f (f x)) = f x := by
      intro x
      exact inverse_spec (f x) ⟨x, rfl⟩
    have h_inv : ∀ x, inverse f (f x) = x := by
      intro x
      apply h
      exact h_spec x
    exact h_inv
  · intro h
    have h_left_inv : ∀ x, f (inverse f (f x)) = f x := by
      intro x
      exact inverse_spec (f x) ⟨x, rfl⟩
    intros x1 x2 e
    have h_x1 : inverse f (f x1) = x1 := h x1
    have h_x2 : inverse f (f x2) = x2 := h x2
    rw [← h_x1, ← h_x2, e]

decl: example : Injective f ↔ LeftInverse (inverse f) f
og_raw:
example : Injective f ↔ LeftInverse (inverse f) f  := by
  ⟨fun h y ↦ h (inverse_spec _ ⟨y, rfl⟩), fun h x1 x2 e ↦ by rw [← h x1, ← h x2, e]⟩
new_raw:
example : Injective f ↔ LeftInverse (inverse f) f  := by
  ⟨fun h y ↦ h (inverse_spec _ ⟨y, rfl⟩), fun h x1 x2 e ↦ by rw [← h x1, ← h x2, e]⟩

decl: example : Surjective f ↔ RightInverse (inverse f) f
og_raw:
example : Surjective f ↔ RightInverse (inverse f) f  := by
  constructor
  · intro h y
    apply inverse_spec
    apply h
  intro h y
  use inverse f y
  apply h
new_raw:
example : Surjective f ↔ RightInverse (inverse f) f   := by
  constructor
  · intro h y
    have h_spec : ∃ x, f x = y := h y
    apply inverse_spec
    exact h_spec
  intro h y
  use inverse f y
  apply h

decl: theorem Cantor : ∀ f : α → Set α, ¬Surjective f
og_raw:
theorem Cantor : ∀ f : α → Set α, ¬Surjective f  := by
  intro f surjf
  let S := { i | i ∉ f i }
  rcases surjf S with ⟨j, h⟩
  have h₁ : j ∉ f j := by
    intro h'
    have : j ∉ f j := by rwa [h] at h'
    contradiction
  have h₂ : j ∈ S := h₁
  have h₃ : j ∉ S := by rwa [h] at h₁
  contradiction
new_raw:

  intro f surjf
  let S := { i | i ∉ f i }
  rcases surjf S with ⟨j, h⟩
  have h₁ : j ∉ f j := by
    intro h'
    have : j ∉ f j := by rwa [h] at h'
    contradiction
  have h₂ : j ∈ S := h₁
  have h₃ : j ∉ S := by rwa [h] at h₁
  contradiction

example {α : Type*} (n : α → Filter α) (H₀ : ∀ a, pure a ≤ n a)
    (H : ∀ a : α, ∀ p : α → Prop, (∀ᶠ x in n a, p x) → ∀ᶠ y in n a, ∀ᶠ x in n y, p x) :
    ∀ a, ∀ s ∈ n a, ∃ t ∈ n a, t ⊆ s ∧ ∀ a' ∈ t, s ∈ n a'

    ∀ a, ∀ s ∈ n a, ∃ t ∈ n a, t ⊆ s ∧ ∀ a' ∈ t, s ∈ n a'  := by

theorem aux {X Y A : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {c : A → X}
      {f : A → Y} {x : X} {F : Filter Y}
      (h : Tendsto f (comap c (𝓝 x)) F) {V' : Set Y} (V'_in : V' ∈ F) :
    ∃ V ∈ 𝓝 x, IsOpen V ∧ c ⁻¹' V ⊆ f ⁻¹' V'   := by
  have basis := (nhds_basis_opens' x).comap c
  have tendsto_comap := basis.tendsto_left_iff.mp h V' V'_in
  simpa [and_assoc] using tendsto_comap

decl:
example [TopologicalSpace X] [TopologicalSpace Y] [T3Space Y] {A : Set X}
    (hA : ∀ x, x ∈ closure A) {f : A → Y} (f_cont : Continuous f)
    (hf : ∀ x : X, ∃ c : Y, Tendsto f (comap (↑) (𝓝 x)) (𝓝 c)) :
    ∃ φ : X → Y, Continuous φ ∧ ∀ a : A, φ a = f a

    ∃ φ : X → Y, Continuous φ ∧ ∀ a : A, φ a = f a  := by
  choose φ hφ using hf
  use φ
  constructor
  · rw [continuous_iff_continuousAt]
    intro x
    suffices ∀ V' ∈ 𝓝 (φ x), IsClosed V' → φ ⁻¹' V' ∈ 𝓝 x by
      simpa [ContinuousAt, (closed_nhds_basis (φ x)).tendsto_right_iff]
    intro V' V'_in V'_closed
    obtain ⟨V, V_in, V_op, hV⟩ : ∃ V ∈ 𝓝 x, IsOpen V ∧ (↑) ⁻¹' V ⊆ f ⁻¹' V' := aux (hφ x) V'_in
    suffices : ∀ y ∈ V, φ y ∈ V'

    haveI : (comap ((↑) : A → X) (𝓝 y)).NeBot := by simpa [mem_closure_iff_comap_neBot] using hA y
    apply V'_closed.mem_of_tendsto (hφ y)
    exact mem_of_superset (preimage_mem_comap hVx) hV
  · intro a
    have lim : Tendsto f (𝓝 a) (𝓝 (φ a)) := by simpa [nhds_induced] using hφ a
    exact tendsto_nhds_unique lim f_cont.continuousAt

decl:
example [TopologicalSpace Y] {f : X → Y} (hf : Continuous f) {s : Set X} (hs : IsCompact s) :
    IsCompact (f '' s)
og_raw:
example [TopologicalSpace Y] {f : X → Y} (hf : Continuous f) {s : Set X} (hs : IsCompact s) :
    IsCompact (f '' s)  := by
  intro F F_ne F_le
  have map_eq : map f (𝓟 s ⊓ comap f F) = 𝓟 (f '' s) ⊓ F := by rw [Filter.push_pull, map_principal]
  have Hne : (𝓟 s ⊓ comap f F).NeBot := by
    apply NeBot.of_map
    rwa [map_eq, inf_of_le_right F_le]
  have Hle : 𝓟 s ⊓ comap f F ≤ 𝓟 s := inf_le_left
  rcases hs Hle with ⟨x, x_in, hx⟩
  refine' ⟨f x, mem_image_of_mem f x_in, _⟩
  apply hx.map hf.continuousAt
  rw [Tendsto, map_eq]
  exact inf_le_right
new_raw:
example [TopologicalSpace Y] {f : X → Y} (hf : Continuous f) {s : Set X} (hs : IsCompact s) :
    IsCompact (f '' s)   := by
  intro F F_ne F_le
  have map_eq : map f (𝓟 s ⊓ comap f F) = 𝓟 (f '' s) ⊓ F := by rw [Filter.push_pull, map_principal]
  have Hne : (𝓟 s ⊓ comap f F).NeBot := by
    apply NeBot.of_map
    rwa [map_eq, inf_of_le_right F_le]
  have Hle : 𝓟 s ⊓ comap f F ≤ 𝓟 s := inf_le_left
  rcases hs Hle with ⟨x, x_in, hx⟩
  have fact1 : x ∈ s := x_in
  have fact2 : ClusterPt x (𝓟 s ⊓ comap f F) := hx
  have fact3 : f x ∈ f '' s := mem_image_of_mem f fact1
  have fact4 : ClusterPt (f x) F := by
    apply fact2.map hf.continuousAt
    rw [Tendsto, map_eq]
    exact inf_le_right
  exact ⟨f x, fact3, fact4⟩
